.\" This file is maintained by hand. Do not edit with cargo xtask man.
.TH NETFYR\-EXAMPLES 7 "" "" "Miscellaneous Information Manual"
.SH NAME
netfyr\-examples \- configuration examples for netfyr
.SH DESCRIPTION
This page shows annotated YAML configuration examples for common
netfyr scenarios.
Each example can be saved to a file in
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/
and applied with
.BR "netfyr apply" .
.PP
For field and format reference, see
.BR netfyr.yaml (5).
.SH "STATIC IP ON A SINGLE INTERFACE"
Assign a static IPv4 address, default gateway, and custom MTU to
an interface identified by name.
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
mtu: 1500
addresses:
  - 10.0.1.50/24
routes:
  - destination: 0.0.0.0/0
    gateway: 10.0.1.1
.fi
.RE
.SH "MULTIPLE INTERFACES IN ONE FILE"
Configure two interfaces in a single file using the multi-document
separator
.BR \-\-\- .
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
mtu: 9000
addresses:
  - 10.0.1.50/24
---
type: ethernet
name: eth1
mtu: 1500
addresses:
  - 192.168.1.10/24
.fi
.RE
.SH "DHCP ON AN INTERFACE"
Acquire an address via DHCPv4.
Requires the netfyr daemon to be running.
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: eth0\-dhcp
factory: dhcpv4
selector:
  name: eth0
.fi
.RE
.SH "MIXED STATIC AND DHCP"
Two files in
.IR /etc/netfyr/policies/ :
one for a static management interface, one for a DHCP uplink.
.PP
File:
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/mgmt.yaml
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
addresses:
  - 192.168.100.1/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
File:
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/uplink.yaml
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: uplink\-dhcp
factory: dhcpv4
selector:
  name: eth1
.fi
.RE
.SH "PRIORITY OVERRIDE"
When two policies set the same field on the same interface, the
higher priority wins.
Here the admin override (priority 200) takes precedence over the
baseline (default priority 100).
.PP
File:
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/baseline.yaml
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
mtu: 1500
.fi
.RE
.PP
File:
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/override.yaml
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: jumbo\-frames
factory: static
priority: 200
state:
  type: ethernet
  name: eth0
  mtu: 9000
.fi
.RE
.PP
Result: eth0 gets mtu 9000 because priority 200 > 100.
.SH "SELECTING BY DRIVER"
Apply jumbo frames to all interfaces using the ixgbe driver,
regardless of interface name.
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
driver: ixgbe
mtu: 9000
.fi
.RE
.SH "DRY\-RUN WORKFLOW"
Preview changes before applying them:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ netfyr apply \-\-dry\-run /etc/netfyr/policies/
ethernet/eth0:
  mtu: 1500 \-> 9000
.fi
.RE
.PP
If the diff looks correct, apply for real:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ netfyr apply /etc/netfyr/policies/
.fi
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR netfyr (1),
.BR netfyr\-apply (1),
.BR netfyr\-query (1),
.BR netfyr\-history (1),
.BR netfyr\-revert (1),
.BR netfyr.yaml (5)
